 <fr:p>Of course, as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is non-empty, it is enough to show that it is not <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link>. We know that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left  [0,1\right  ]\mathclose {}}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\to {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}\cong  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and and it follows from <fr:ref
addr="jms-00NF"
href="jms-00NF.xml"
taxon="Theorem" /> that the latter is not <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
