title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Consider the subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U\in \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> defined below:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   U = {\mathopen {}\left \{x\in  A\,\middle \vert \,x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}\right \}\mathclose {}}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>, we may find some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=U]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Thus for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we have
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[    x\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}    \Longleftrightarrow     x\in  U    \Longleftrightarrow     x\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}  ]]></fr:tex>. Setting <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:= a]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} \Longleftrightarrow  a\not \in  e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, a contradiction.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
